AWS Local Zones
- Places AWS compute, storage, database, and other selected AWS services closer to end users to run latency-sensitive applications
- Extend your VPC to more locations: "Extension of an AWS Region"
- Compatible with EC2, RDS, ECS, EBS, ElastiCache, Direct Connect...



Global Applications Architecture
- Single Region, Single AZ
  - No high availability
  - No global latency
  - Difficulty: Very easy
- Single Region, Multi AZ
  - High availability
  - No global latency
  - Difficulty: easy
- Multi-Region: Active-Passive
  - Multiple regions with one active EC2 instance and one passive EC2 instance
  - Global Reads' Latency
  - No Global Writes' Latency
  - Difficulty: medium
- Multi_Region: Active-Active
  - Multiple regions with all active EC2 instances
  - Global Reads' Latency
  - Global Writes' Latency
  - Difficulty: High
